==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hostilities
<hw>hostilities</hw> <pos>n. pl.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a legal state
created by a declaration of war and ended by official declaration,
during which the international rules of war apply.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> war, state of war, hot war.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><q>We have showed ourselves generous adversaries . . . and have
carried on even our <qex>hostilities</qex> with humanity.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>acts of overt warfare.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> belligerency.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hostility</ent>⟦br⟧
